  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b85\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9c\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd 244 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0bc2\u0baa\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Japan has provided 244 million rupees for demining in the north",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Government of Japan provides 244 million rupees for demining work in the North The Government of Japan has provided financial assistance of about 244 million rupees to continue the ongoing demining activities in the North.",
        "With the donation of the Government of Japan, the DOS demining team is carrying out demining operations in the Mullaitivu districts of Kilinochchi.",
        "The Japanese government has donated $ 681,812 (approximately Rs. 244 million) to DASH through its Grant Assistance for Grassroots Human Security Projects (GGP) project for humanitarian demining work in the northern region of Sri Lanka.",
        "The signing ceremony was held this morning (28) at the DASH Operation Area, Muhamalai, Kilinochchi District, attended by Japanese Ambassador to Sri Lanka Misukoshi Hideki and DASH Program Manager Ananda Chandrasiri.",
        "Since 2010, DASH has cleared 15 square kilometers of landmines. Of this, 6.5 sq km was cleared and released through the Japanese government's GGP assistance program.",
        "Ananda Chandrasiri, Program Manager, DASH, said, \"Japan's assistance to DASH, Japan Government's assistance in the face of the current economic crisis in Sri Lanka, has also saved the livelihoods of 135 demining families.",
        "This year marks the 70th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between Japan and Sri Lanka. It is a key component of the Japanese Official Development Assistance Program for Sri Lanka in relation to development in the war-affected area. He added that the Japanese government expects to continue to contribute to the Sri Lankan government's goal of achieving a \"landmine-free Sri Lanka\"."
      ],
